ics”; as well as to intellectual issues which cut across the conventional classification of schools. The main focus is on the high cultural texts, but Mr. Schwartz also explores the question of the relationship of these texts to the vast realm of popular culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aPhilosophy, ChineseyTo 221 B.C. 7aHISTORY / Asia / China.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/9780674043312zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674043312423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674043312/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK